pageContext.claim: “Dr. Robert Redfield. He was totally misquoted in the media on a statement about the fall season and the virus. Totally misquoted.”
pageContext.analysis: Redfield came to the podium and acknowledged, "I'm accurately quoted in the Washington Post." He said he had an issue with the headline on the article. Nevertheless, he had tweeted the article after it was published -- before Trump got angry over it.
